Durban- A teenager who was found dead in the ceiling of a shop in Pietermaritzburg was suspected to be a burglar and was trying to exit the roof at the time of his death, police have confirmed. KZN police spokesperson Lt Colonel Thulani Zwane said it was the shop owner who made the discovery and notified police and other relevant authorities. Zwane said it is believed the teenager was a suspected robber and had been attempting to exit the roof when he was electrocuted. "A case of burglary and [an] inquest has been opened at Pietermaritzburg SAPS or investigation." According to Russel Meiring from ER24 paramedics were called to scene at around 6:30am. "SAPS Search and Rescue were already in attendance.Â ER24 medics climbed into the ceiling and found the motionless boy lying inside the ceiling. Search and Rescue Services had to cut away part of the roof to gain access to the patient. "Once freed, medics assessed the man and found that he had sustained burn wounds to his arms and showed no signs of life. Nothing could be done for him and he was declared dead," said Meiring. POST